name: Belville Riverwalk Park
street: Across from Belville Elementary at 575 River Rd SE Leland, NC 28451
directions: Exit Highway 17 heading south toward Southport on 133. Belville Elementary will be on the right. The park is on your left.
comment: They have recently (at least as of June 20, 2015) opened up a new trailhead at one of my favorite parks to relax and meditate in. If you follow the trail you will come to a Duke Energy Pavilion. There are some round tables and a gender neutral bathroom. It was locked when I went, and the trail still needs to be fully cleared. There are older restrooms too near the parking lot, but those are not gender neutral. However, I have gone in the women's bathroom dressed as myself several times without incident.

name: Grand Central Building
directions: Restroom is below the main floor (downstairs).This a building with several businesses in it. You need a code for the lock (when I was there it was 2525) it may have changed, if you ask someone in one of the businesses for it nicely they will give you the code (we asked the Salon, after eating at Owl Soda Fountain).
comment:
CLEAN. Self flushing toilet, urinal, clearly labeled unisex restroom. Locking door. Single occupancy. Away from the main hustle and bustle.
 Two entrances to the building, one upstairs and one below. I wrote non accessible even though it  LOOKED big enough for a wheelchair and the second entrance is downstairs from inside the building BUT only down a mini hill from outside (partial basement). I failed to notice if it was labeled as such or whether it had bars. If you find out please adjust this entry.
